image_analysis.description: A photograph showing a set of indoor stairs. The stairs are covered in a grey, patterned carpet. There is a wooden handrail on the left side supported by blue-painted metal balusters. The walls are painted an off-white or light cream color. A blue-painted baseboard runs along the wall following the incline of the stairs. A small portion of a ceiling light fixture is visible at the top center. An electrical outlet is visible on the wall near the landing.
image_analysis.layout: Vertical orientation showing a perspective view looking up a staircase.

notes: The image is a standard photograph used as evidence or documentation, identified by the Bates stamp in the bottom right corner.
